{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778092517,"nonce":"xqoeio53cnpAj121ArasWHrjwb0=","message":"## Riccati production implementation results (5a44bd3)\n\nMerged. All 16 tests pass.\n\n**Headline magnitudes:**\n- **rlrmp regime** (k=10, τ=0.05): γ* = 0.0094; Δv at 1.05γ* = +12.82%; Δv at 1.5γ* = +5.44%. Direction matches synthesis_review §10's prediction; magnitude is at the lower bound of the +10–25% range. Phase 2 reported +10.8% at 1.5γ* — production figure ~2× smaller, consistent with proper conditioning.\n- **C\u0026S regime** (k=0.1, τ=0.06): γ* = 0.0116; |Δv| \u003c 2.5% across γ ∈ [1.05γ*, 5γ*]; Δv at 1.5γ* = -0.77%. Sign-flipped vs Phase 2's +1.5% — both small in magnitude. **See follow-up comment for the Q,R-schedule caveat.**\n\n**Production-quality wins vs Phase 2** (which used float32 + explicit-inverse and blew up near γ*):\n- Numerical conditioning: max bracket condition \u003c 4×10³ across γ ∈ [1.05γ*, 5γ*].\n- Boundary detection: γ slightly below γ* flagged inadmissible cleanly without NaN.\n- LQR limit: ‖K_LQR - K_H∞(γ=10⁶)‖ / ‖K_LQR‖ \u003c 10⁻⁸.\n- Linearization fidelity vs diffrax-integrated PointMass ODE: \u003c 10⁻⁷ over 100 timesteps.\n\n**Conditioning strategy:** double precision throughout (`jax_enable_x64`), `jnp.linalg.solve` instead of explicit inverse, per-step admissibility check (spectral radius `λ_max(γ⁻² B_w^T P B_w)` and bracket condition number).\n\nModule + tests at `src/rlrmp/analysis/hinf_riccati.py` + `tests/test_hinf_riccati.py`. Also added `pytest\u003e=8.0` as the minimal dev dep (rlrmp had no test infrastructure prior).","files":null}]}